    "attributes": {
        "action": "Revoke Article 50 & give Brexit back to the people through a Citizen\u2019s Assembly.",
        "additional_details": "Parliament gave this sovereign decision to the people but did not adequately inform the public of options and likely consequences.  Following the 2016 vote, Parliament has failed to come together and agree to act in our best interests. It is now time for Parliament to give this issue back to the people, without time constraints, and with better information, for the people to find a way forward in an informed way that respects us as one nation.",
        "background": "The UK government has not properly dealt with this issue. Prior to the 2016 referendum renegotiation of our membership by the PM failed. During the referendum a coherent plan for leave was not made. Following the referendum Parliament has failed to identify a way forward that is in our interests.",
